.TH "RALPHISH" "1" "March 2026" "" ""
.
.SH "NAME"
\fBralphish\fR \- loop a CLI command until DONE
.
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
\fBralphish\fR [\fB\-t\fR|\fB\-\-timeout\fR \fIminutes\fR] [\fB\-c\fR|\fB\-\-cmd\fR \fIcommand\fR] \fIprompt\fR
.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
\fBralphish\fR is a minimal Ralph Wiggum Loop for fish shell\. It repeatedly runs a CLI command with the given prompt until the output contains \fB<PROMPT>DONE</PROMPT>\fR, indicating the task is complete\.
.
.P
Each iteration (round) runs \fB<command> \-p <prompt>\fR and checks the output\. If the round times out, the next round\'s prompt is appended with a note about the timeout\. Output from each round is displayed via \fBbat\fR\.
.
.P
Designed for use with Claude Code skills that maintain their own state machines and output \fB<PROMPT>DONE</PROMPT>\fR when they reach a terminal state\.
.
.P
A pidfile is written to \fB/tmp/ralphish\.<pid>\.pid\fR on startup\. The loop continues as long as this file exists\.
.
.SH "OPTIONS"
.
.TP
\fB\-t\fR, \fB\-\-timeout\fR \fIminutes\fR
Per\-round timeout in minutes\. Defaults to 30\. Requires \fBgtimeout\fR or \fBtimeout\fR to be available on the system\.
.
.TP
\fB\-c\fR, \fB\-\-cmd\fR \fIcommand\fR
The CLI command to run each round\. Defaults to \fBclaude \-\-dangerously\-skip\-permissions\fR\.
.
.SH "STOPPING"
.
.IP "\(bu" 4
\fBGraceful stop\fR: Remove the pidfile\. The current round finishes, then ralphish exits\.
.
.IP "" 4
.
.nf

rm /tmp/ralphish\.<pid>\.pid
.
.fi
.
.IP "" 0

.
.IP "\(bu" 4
\fBHard stop\fR: Kill the process directly\.
.
.IP "" 4
.
.nf

kill <pid>
.
.fi
.
.IP "" 0

.
.IP "" 0
.
.P
Both the pidfile path and PID are printed at startup\.
.
.SH "EXAMPLES"
Run with default 30\-minute timeout:
.
.IP "" 4
.
.nf

ralphish "Fix the failing tests in src/"
.
.fi
.
.IP "" 0
.
.P
Run with a 10\-minute per\-round timeout:
.
.IP "" 4
.
.nf

ralphish \-t 10 "Refactor the auth module"
.
.fi
.
.IP "" 0
.
.P
Use a custom CLI command:
.
.IP "" 4
.
.nf

ralphish \-c "claude \-\-model opus" "Fix the flaky test"
.
.fi
.
.IP "" 0
.
